        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} Related. His aunts, their men and the kids of his cousin. Oh and dog Oscar not to forget. After arrival we enjoyed a relaxing afternoon with dogs, cakes on the terrace, followed by a few round table tennis. The pool attracted, and although I originally only wanted to go in with my feet, the two kids made it impossible to stay dry. I was quickly in the water - a welcome fun, which we all laughed at. </p>
        <p> In the evening, the day was rounded off with a delicious grill meal and cool drinks. We slowly ended the day in nice conversations, but we knew that the next day would be exciting again. </p>
        <p> Today the day started calmly with a cozy breakfast, where we were spoiled with cooked eggs and other treats. Steffi further crawled Oscar into the ground. We discussed that we would stay until Monday before going to the Elbeandstein Mountains. Strengthened we set off at lunchtime to meet with Kerstin, Thomas and the two girls for a hike. </p>
        <p> It started with a little confusion when we ended up in the wrong parking lot. But Uncle Thomas, who came to us, drove the 500 meters to the right meeting point. The hike then really started: first a small round around the lake and then off into the forest to the Muldenberg Dam. Steffi went in front at some point without great motivation - her motto: "When I stop, I won't get any further!" </p>

