        <p> After about eight kilometers we reached the Fl&ouml;&szlig;erstube in Muldenberg and treated ourselves to cakes and drinks. We decided almost unanimously to take the way back. On the way to the train, the girls still had fun when they pulled themselves over a pool with a raft. </p>
        <p> Back in Sch&ouml;neck, we said goodbye to aunt, uncle and the girls, but took some time to explore the IFA holiday complex. There is really a lot to discover here - hiking trails, ski courses, wellness programs and much more. After a small dinner in the hotel we drove back to Aunt Babsi and Uwe, who were still on the move. We made it comfortable in front of TV, played a round and talked until the two of them came back. Then it was time to go to bed and digest the experiences of the day. </p>
        <p> So it was a day full of beautiful experiences. We would be happy to take many more! Until tomorrow </p>
